President Joe Biden welcomed the 2021 NBA champions, the Milwaukee Bucks, to the White House. He congratulated the team owners, including Ted and Mary Kellner, who had supported Biden's Senate campaign in 1972. Biden also acknowledged the previous team owner, Herb Kohl, and commended the players, including MVP Giannis Antetokounmpo and Donte DiVincenzo, who was the Delaware high school basketball Player of the Year in 2015. Biden praised the team for their resilience and teamwork throughout the playoffs, and their efforts off the court, such as standing up for justice and encouraging vaccinations. He emphasized the unity and values represented by the sport of basketball and expressed his hope to see the Bucks return to the White House next year. President Biden was presented with a Bucks jersey during the event.